title: Three-star WR Trevion Armstrong commits to Nevada
text: Share Updated: 10/09 11:58 pm RENO, Nev. (Mynews4.com & KRNV) -- Recruiting never stops for the Nevada football team and on Friday the Pack landed a three-star WR commitment from Virginia - Trevion Robinson.Robinson, who hails from Trininty High School in Richmond, Virginia, announced via his Twitter page and in front of friends and family at the school's athletic center.The 6-foot-4, 210 pounder chose the Wolf Pack over Illinois, Pittsburgh, and Toledo.Armstrong visited Nevada last weekend and was shown around by fellow Virginian and Nevada freshman defensive back Cal Kee III.
